
LKM := Loadable Kernel Module

How to create LKMs:
1. write source file: lkm.c
2. write Makefile: Makefile
3. kernel module utilities:
	modinfo: show module information
	modprobe: load modules which the current module dependents
	insmod: only load the current module
4. see module output information using `dmesg | tail`

link: www.thegeekstuff.com/2012/04/linux-lkm-basics/
